ASL Perfusion CBF by FreeSurfer ROI

Source: R/data.R
UCSFASLFSCBF.Rd

ASL Perfusion CBF by FreeSurfer ROI data. More information is available at https://adni.loni.usc.edu/data-samples/adni-data/

Usage

data(UCSFASLFSCBF)

Format

A data frame with 515 observations and 438 variables.

Source

https://adni.loni.usc.edu/data-samples/adni-data/

Details

  • ORIGPROT character Original study protocol , with options: ADNI1, ADNI2, ADNI3, ADNIGO

  • COLPROT character Study protocol of data collection , with options: ADNI3

  • PTID character Participant Identifier for the in-clinic ADNI study

  • RID numeric Participant Identifier for the in-clinic ADNI study Range value: 21, ..., 7092

  • VISCODE character VISCODE of the Image , with options: y1, y2, init, sc, y4, y3, y5

  • VISCODE2 character Translated visit code

  • IMAGEUID numeric Image UID of image that was processed. Range value: 812264, ..., 1691094

  • EXAMDATE When the image was collected. Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • RUNDATE When the image was processed. Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • ASLFLAVOR character The dimensionality and pulse sequence of the ASL acquisition , with options: SIEMENS3DPASL, 3DPCASL, SIEMENS2DPASL, PHILIPS2DPASL

  • CBFQC character Checks the qCBF overlaid on the PD image , with options: Pass, Fail

  • SEGQC character Checks the PD (M0) to T1 registration , with options: Pass, Fail

  • REGQC character Checks the FreeSurfer aparc+aseg in T1 space , with options: Pass, Fail

  • FSOVERALLQC character An overall quality rating. Refer to additional QC variables for Partial rating. , with options: Pass, Partial

  • FSTEMPQC character QC rating of temporal lobe. Fail affects the following regions: LeftTemporalPole (ST60); RightTemporalPole (ST119); LeftFusiform (ST26); RightFusiform (ST85); LeftSuperiorTemporal (ST58); RightSuperiorTemporal (ST117); LeftInferiorTemporal (ST32); RightInferiorTemporal (ST91); LeftMiddleTemporal (ST40); RightMiddleTemporal (ST99) , with options: Pass, Fail

  • FSFRONTQC character QC rating of the frontal lobe. Fail affects the following regions: LeftFrontalPole (ST25); RightFrontalPole (ST84); LeftPrecentral (ST51); RightPrecentral (ST110); LeftSuperiorFrontal (ST56); RightSuperiorFrontal (ST115); LeftCaudalMiddleFrontal (ST15); RightCaudalMiddleFrontal (ST74); LeftRostralMiddleFrontal (ST55); RightRostralMiddleFrontal (ST114); LeftMedialOrbitofrontal (ST39); RightMedialOrbitofrontal (ST98) , with options: Pass, Fail

  • FSPARQC character QC rating of the parietal lobe. Fail affects the following regions: LeftPostcentral (ST49); RightPostcentral (ST108); LeftSuperiorParietal (ST57); RightSuperiorParietal (ST116); LeftSupraMarginal (ST59); RightSupraMarginal (ST118); LeftParacentral (ST43); RightParacentral (ST102); LeftInferiorParietal (ST31); RightInferiorParietal (ST90) , with options: Pass, Fail

  • FSINSULAQC character QC rating of the insula. Fail affects the following regions: LeftInsula (ST129); RightInsula (ST130) , with options: Pass, Fail

  • FSOCCQC character QC rating of the occipital lobe. Fail affects the following regions: LeftLingual (ST38); RightLingual (ST97); LeftLateralOccipital (ST35); RightLateralOccipital (ST94); LeftPericalcarine (ST48); RightPericalcarine (ST107); LeftCuneus (ST23); RightCuneus (ST82) , with options: Pass, Fail

  • FSBGQC character QC rating of the basal ganglia. Fail affects the following regions: LeftPutamen (ST53); RightPutamen (ST112); LeftCaudate (ST16); RightCaudate (ST75); LeftPallidum (ST42); RightPallidum (ST101) , with options: Pass, Fail

  • FSCWMQC character QC rating of the cerebral WM. Fail affects the following regions: LeftCerebralWM (ST20); RightCerebralWM (ST79); LeftCorticalWM (ST150); RightCorticalWM (ST151); CorticalWM (ST152); LeftHemisphereWM (ST28); RightHemisphereWM (ST87) , with options: Pass, Fail

  • FSVENTQC character QC rating of the ventricles. Fail affects the following regions: LeftLateralVentricle (ST37); RightLateralVentricle (ST96); LeftInferiorLateralVentricle (ST30); RightInferiorLateralVentricle (ST89); ThirdVentricle (ST127); FourthVentricle (ST9); FifthVentrical (ST8); LeftChoroidPlexus (ST21); RightChoroidPlexus (ST80) , with options: Pass, Fail
